<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7139&amp;p=30659#p30659"><![CDATA[
With Classic Shell installed, you could capture a crash dump using these steps: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=12&amp;t=6">viewtopic.php?f=12&amp;t=6</a><!-- l --> using Command Prompt and Task Manager.<br /><br />Once the cause of the Explorer crash is determined by analyzing the dump, it can be fixed (if it is caused by Classic Shell). Then you will be able to use the non-crashing version.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Dec 01, 2016 10:26 pm</p><hr />
