<title type="html"><![CDATA[After install, explorer will not start on bootup]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7139&amp;p=30655#p30655"><![CDATA[
As Classic Shell appears to be the only way to customize the taskbar background (glass and transparency are lovely), I installed it. The only changes I ended up applying were to the taskbar, which I made more transparent, and applied the aero glass style. I didn't end up using any of the start menu changes or anything like that, as I like and am used to the overall layout of Windows 10. The program worked perfectly fine until I restarted my computer. <br /><br />Upon a reboot, Windows Explorer will not start at all. I was unable to access my files or desktop. The rest of Windows, such as the Task Manager, Command Prompt, and Uninstall menu worked perfectly fine. I used them to uninstall Classic Shell, which fixed the problem after a restart. <br /><br />I'd like to know if there's any known way to fix this problem, cos the taskbar looks kinda wierd being the only non-glass element on my PC, and I'd like to fix that. I am using Windows 10, and the only other Windows desktop modification programs I have running are Aero Glass and Rainmeter. I used the latest available stable version of Classic Shell (4.3.0). <br /><br />This was a few weeks ago, for the record. I've been trying to find a solution since, but... nothing.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=16475">KicksBrickster</a> — Thu Dec 01, 2016 7:37 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
